{"article_id":"2OOYRfWb1bkrTFoI","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"On Tuesday , 14 states voted in the Democratic presidential primary .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"\" Joe Biden swept through the South","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"and earned surprise victories in Massachusetts and Minnesota ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"while Bernie Sanders held serve in the West. \"","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"Politico","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"Both sides see the results as a clear win for Biden and a major setback for Sanders .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"\" Political junkies figured","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"Biden was on the road to oblivion","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"and that Bernie Sanders was moving inexorably toward the nomination .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"But [ a ] time traveler would have said ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"' Wait a minute .","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"Nobody thought","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"Biden would actually win Iowa or New Hampshire .","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"His plan was always to win big in South Carolina","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"and use that","depth":14},{"id":15,"text":"to barrel ahead on Super Tuesday. '","depth":14},{"id":16,"text":"... it looks like Biden didn ' t need very much","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"to get himself back on the very same track","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"he had laid out for himself","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"when he started running last April .","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"If that ' s right ,","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"then there was never any Biden collapse .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"What happened to him was a predictable bump on the road . \"","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"\" We 've seen candidates skip Iowa ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"fail to win New Hampshire ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"and then go on to secure their party 's nomination .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"But competing in both ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"finishing fourth and fifth ,","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"and then ending up the frontrunner ?","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"That 's unheard of","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"- and it calls into question not just whether those two small and unrepresentative states should come first on the calendar ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"but whether the way","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"they vote","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"deserves outsized attention at all...","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Biden also showed","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"that money does n't matter as much","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"as many of us tend to assume","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"it does .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"The Biden campaign was outspent 7-to-1 by the Sanders camp and an astonishing 100-to-1 by the Bloomberg juggernaut in the states","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that competed on Super Tuesday...","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"\" Biden 's remarkable reversal of fortune this past week shows","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"that the party decides presidential nominations after all","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"or at least it can still do so","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"when the stakes are sufficiently high","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and leading members of the party resolve to intervene .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Tuesday 's results simply could n't have happened","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"had the institutional party not engaged in an astoundingly rapid act of consolidation","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"- against Sanders and in favor of Biden .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"\" \" Sanders himself declared victory with just two states under his belt...","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"' We are going to win , '","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"he continued","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"as his fans chanted","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"BER-NEE , BER-NEE ,","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"' we are going to defeat Trump","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"because we are putting together an unprecedented grassroots multigenerational multiracial movement ' .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"That movement somehow doesn ' t include African Americans in the south...","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Sanders ' victory in California will be a source of hope for his campaign .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"But scraping out a slender delegate lead is not the same as a multigenerational , multiracial movement","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"to beat Trump...","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"\" Every single exit poll in the Democratic contests have stressed a single factor :","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"beating Trump .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"In the states","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"that voted on Tuesday ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"between 60 and 70 % of Democrats said","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"they preferred a candidate","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"who could beat Trump","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"over someone","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"they agreed with on the issues...","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"Super Tuesday ' s super wins for Biden change nothing about his flaws ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"but they do underscore the strength of his sales pitch to a Trump-weary world . \"","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"\" Overall , the story of Super Tuesday is the utter collapse in momentum for Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"The African-American vote has just come out in massive numbers for Biden in state after state ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"while there ' s no sign of that massive wave of new and younger voters","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"that Sanders promised .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"Bernie still has a good chance","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"of winning the nomination ,","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"but the Democratic Party ' s establishment pulled its act together at the last minute ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"and it looks like a long , hard fight all the way to Milwaukee... \"","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Democrats may well end up with some buyer ' s remorse ;","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Biden is the same guy","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"who unnerved so many Democrats with his aging appearance , forgetfulness , and gaffes .","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"But the party establishment has put its doubts aside","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"and decided to ride","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"or die with him .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"After a long , cacophonous noise , the Democratic primary is down to two extremely different candidates . \"","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":171,"left":0,"right":170,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":170,"left":88,"right":169,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":88,"left":87,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":87,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":4,"right":168,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":168,"left":5,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":127,"right":166,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":121,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":104,"right":120,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":104,"left":90,"right":103,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":90,"left":6,"right":89,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":89,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":103,"left":96,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":9,"right":95,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":95,"left":10,"right":94,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":91,"right":93,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":91,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":13,"right":92,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":99,"right":101,"rela